Regular backing
---------------
Window constructor creates Bitmap
Bitmap creates Buffer
Buffer allocates memory

Hardware backing for window
---------------------------
Window constructor creates Bitmap
Bitmap creates DRMFramebuffer
DRMFramebuffer requests overlay DRMPlane (fails if there are none free - fall back to regular in caller?)
DRMPlane is attached to DRMCRTC (from DisplayManager)
DRMFramebuffer allocates memory via DRM API

Window destructor destroys Bitmap
~Bitmap destroys DRMFramebuffer
~DRMFramebuffer releases DRMPlane (marks as unused)

Hardware backing for cursor/root widget
---------------------------------------
Constructor creates Bitmap
Bitmap creates DRMFramebuffer
DRMFramebuffer requests cursor/primary DRMPlane from DRMCRTC (fails if there are none free - fall back to regular in caller?) -- or does it request a cursor/primary plane then attach it to the CRTC?
DRMFramebuffer allocates memory via DRM API

Cursor destructor destroys Bitmap
~Bitmap destroys DRMFramebuffer
~DRMFramebuffer releases DRMPlane (marks as unused)